<br>
   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Premise of the Deck:<br>
<br>
The deck is geared to using Zannah to gain a nice card/creature advantage over your opponent.  By using her charm ability you can really maximize this advantage.  The deck utilizes 2 Relic Stalkers to help prevent any other relics that may work against this, ie: Rayje&#39;s Belt and Rayje&#39;s Sword etc.  Usually Zannah can handle 2 magi on her own.  This leads into Tiller who can uses Scrounge, Exchange, and Vortex enough extra cards into your hand for a 1 turn win over the 3rd magi.  Tryn follows in the last slot as a reserve magi that can hold her own with the best.  Using her Refresh power and and of the bigger creatures you may have in your hand, i.e. Forest Hyrens, Giant Carillions, Ormagon, you can usually stroll to victory with her.<br>
<br>
Detailed Engines:<br>
Balamants: Reach out and hit that magi with 1 energy and no creatures during your second Powers/Spells/Relics phase.<br>
<br>
Vim and Vigor: Playing another Naroom deck with a really big weebo?  Or Voda got a creature just a little to beefy?  Downside that chap with Vim and Vigor.<br>
<br>
Essence of Naroom: Depending on your local meta you can run 1 or 2.  Lots of Naroom/Weave decks in your area need 2 of these in your deck.<br>
<br>
Bungaloo: They are cute and you will always get back what you pay with them.<br>
<br>
Ormagon: Clear the board when/if needed.  Great for when you just need a fresh start.<br>
<br>
Thunderquakes: Gets around Zannah&#39;s effect and is a great way to clear weenies.<br>
<br>
Combos:<br>
<br>
Weebo + Giant Carillion: Stomp, and heal<br>
Weebo + Forest Hyren: Insane way to get energy moving around.  Add in a Vim and Vigor to get your magi some of that goodness. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
